    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-09T20:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-09T20:40:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1040.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-09T21:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1914, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dominican Government has met requirements insisted upon by Legation and has
                    placed all political prisoners under jurisdiction of courts, conceding rights to
                    trial not before enjoyed here. Congress proceeded in orderly manner with
                    business in hand; The country enjoying unusual tranquillity and the only danger
                    lies in the crying need for financial relief. Dominican Government meeting its
                    current expenses by borrowing small amounts from day to day securing all sums
                    with the greatest difficulty. The danger of this Government falling, which is
                    serious, should be avoided until elections are held and it should be financed in
                    some way during the interval. Any succeeding provisional government would be
                    compelled to sacrifice every source of revenue to keep alive. Mailing financial
                    data requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
